      "post_content": "One of the more fair targeted Land Destruction cards that anyone would actually use.  \n  \nLands that blow up other Lands are just much more useful for realistic deckbuilding though. Land Destruction as a strategy wants to as close to 1-for-1 or better the whole battlefield's mana, so that a card like Jayemdae Tome or something can net you an advantage. 2 or 3 mana is the most I think people will actually pay to kill a land.",
